Our metric, based on the fundamental constraint of optical passivity, allows us to describe the maximal power conversion efficiency of an integrated SP source and provides physical insights on how to attain this upper efficiency34. We compare different gated FEA designs from the literature36,37,39–41, in which intensity-voltage relations have been measured. FEA are usually characterized by their Fowler-Nordheim (FN)38 coefficients aFN and bFN2lnIAV GE2= lnaFN-bFNV GE\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
